# Discussion 1

### Initial Planning Meeting

We began by reviewing the project requirements and discussing what reproducibility means in the context of machine learning research. After reading the assignment instructions, we agreed that our goal was not to redesign the models but to verify whether the authors' published results could be reproduced using the provided code and datasets.

We selected the paper *Detection of COVID-19 Epidemic Outbreak Using Machine Learning* because the authors made both their code and data publicly available. Before running anything, we explored the repository structure to understand the workflow. We identified three main components: data preprocessing (`make_data.py`), model training (`training.py`), and figure generation (`figure.ipynb`).

During the initial setup, we encountered a few issues related to the execution environment. The repository was originally developed for a local Python environment, while we were working in Google Colab. Some file paths had to be adjusted, and we spent time verifying that all required packages were installed. We also discussed whether we should modify the original code but agreed to keep the implementation unchanged except for environment-related adjustments.

By the end of this discussion, we had a clear execution plan and divided the work so that each team member could independently verify different stages of the reproduction process while documenting observations throughout the project.
